DESCRIPTION

A program to rotate the characters in a string an arbitraty number of
characters. It must perserve non-letter characters and capitalization. The
string must NOT be rotated in place.

USAGE

./rot <factor> <string>  -- rotate each character in <string> by <factor> letters.

EXAMPLES

> ./rot 13 'Hello World'
Uryyb Jbeyq

> ./rot 14 'Hello World'
Vszzc Kcfzr

> ./rot -14 'Vszzc Kcfzr'
Hello World

> ./rot 182 'Hello World'
Hello World
